1
00:00:04,250 --> 00:00:07,099
♫ Nowhere to escape. ♫

2
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:10,059
♫ No bough to alight. ♫

3
00:00:10,060 --> 00:00:14,130
♫ Retrograde with smile. ♫

4
00:00:16,060 --> 00:00:18,969
♫ Never give in. ♫

5
00:00:18,970 --> 00:00:24,050
♫ Forget about the youth. ♫

6
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:29,019
♫ I've never been afraid of loneliness. ♫

7
00:00:29,020 --> 00:00:31,889
♫ I also shed the tears of regret. ♫

8
00:00:31,890 --> 00:00:34,889
♫ But my heart is still fiery-hot. ♫

9
00:00:34,890 --> 00:00:37,939
♫ To the distance. ♫

10
00:00:37,940 --> 00:00:41,009
♫ The miserable past is like a dagger. ♫

11
00:00:41,010 --> 00:00:43,819
♫ Though my wings are broken, ♫

12
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:49,940
♫ I will keep flying. ♫

13
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:56,299
♫ Following the light, ♫

14
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,459
♫ I'll forget you. ♫

15
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:04,259
♫ The memory shaped my stubbornness. ♫

16
00:01:04,260 --> 00:01:07,459
♫ By virtue of the light in the dark night, ♫

17
00:01:07,460 --> 00:01:10,409
♫ I'll return it with a long ballad. ♫

18
00:01:10,410 --> 00:01:12,369
♫ The river of life is under my feet. ♫

19
00:01:12,370 --> 00:01:16,860
♫ I don't regret my craziness. ♫

20
00:01:26,330 --> 00:01:32,799
The Long Ballad

21
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:42,558
Episode 26

22
00:01:42,559 --> 00:01:43,720
Now my mother is dead,

23
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,359
I want to realize her last wish.

24
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,960
I want to look at this world.

25
00:01:51,439 --> 00:01:55,238
If father has a fit person to take charge of Eagle Division,

26
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:57,798
please ask him to take good care of Eagle Division.

27
00:01:57,799 --> 00:02:02,838
Sun, on this grassland, apart from Sun,

28
00:02:02,839 --> 00:02:05,759
no one is qualified to be the Tegin of Eagle Division.

29
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:09,559
No matter where I go, Ashile Tribe would be in my heart forever.

30
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:12,928
Please let me go, Father!

31
00:02:12,929 --> 00:02:14,729
Sun,

32
00:02:14,730 --> 00:02:19,609
you know, father has cultivated you so hard since you were young,

33
00:02:19,610 --> 00:02:21,809
I placed great hope on you.

34
00:02:21,810 --> 00:02:25,289
Why are you flinching now, Sun?

35
00:02:27,010 --> 00:02:31,329
I have been thinking that as long as I am strong enough,

36
00:02:33,329 --> 00:02:35,288
I could protect everyone.

37
00:02:35,289 --> 00:02:37,569
But now, I can hardly protect my own mother.

38
00:02:39,218 --> 00:02:41,578
Maybe I am not the hero on this grassland.

39
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,560
Please let your son go.

40
00:02:47,239 --> 00:02:48,638
I don't want to compete with anyone.

41
00:02:48,639 --> 00:02:51,039
Why do you improperly belittle yourself?

42
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,559
I have done my best.

43
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:55,600
If I knew this, I shouldn't have done those things.

44
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,400
Let me leave.

45
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,200
Then I will let you go.

46
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:15,999
But you have to remember,

47
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:25,760
no matter where you are, your father loves you forever.

48
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,879
Sun, I don't expect you to forgive me.

49
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:40,560
I just hope that after I leave, you would get rid of a burden.

50
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,079
Don't suffer from me.

51
00:03:47,999 --> 00:03:48,999
Come on.

52
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,599
This girl is in some kind of trouble.

53
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:58,479
Everyone has his or her own difficulty.

54
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,800
Since she doesn't want to tell you, why bother to ask her?

55
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,960
That makes sense.

56
00:04:03,999 --> 00:04:08,959
But, grandpa, can we change a horse when we get to the next town?

57
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:12,518
Look at this donkey, Little Gourd is about to give birth.

58
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:14,959
How could she drag us three?

59
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,078
It's too slow.

60
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,560
When can we arrive?

61
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,839
The donkey is good enough.

62
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:23,838
You, young people, have so much time left, why in such a hurry?

63
00:04:23,839 --> 00:04:24,839
Drink tea.

64
00:04:25,879 --> 00:04:26,879
Fine.

65
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:31,958
Do you know that due to your impulsion, Alir died,

66
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:33,359
what would the consequence be like?

67
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,919
I was wrong.

68
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,118
Please punish me, Uncle Khan.

69
00:04:37,119 --> 00:04:38,119
Punish?

70
00:04:39,439 --> 00:04:43,998
If I punish you, could Alir come back to life?

71
00:04:43,999 --> 00:04:49,878
Do you know that Alir is the only one Sun cares about in his life?

72
00:04:49,879 --> 00:04:53,199
The biggest advantage of Sun is not his ability to lead troops,

73
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,438
but he got the hearts of all the people in Eagle Division.

74
00:04:56,439 --> 00:05:00,398
But from now on, I can never control Eagle Division.

75
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:05,639
Now Ashile Tribe is in disorder, and I lost my Eagle Division,

76
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:09,920
When can I get my strength back and fight the south?

77
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:12,959
Crap!

78
00:05:13,959 --> 00:05:15,040
Just a bunch of crap!

79
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:29,558
The root cause of her disease is not just a wound,

80
00:05:29,559 --> 00:05:32,919
but a mental trauma.

81
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:36,759
According to her pulse condition, she is dispirited,

82
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:39,118
with no hope for life.

83
00:05:39,119 --> 00:05:45,080
She doesn't want to live, even the god can't help her.

84
00:05:49,719 --> 00:05:51,438
Why are you looking at me?

85
00:05:51,439 --> 00:05:52,799
I can only save her.

86
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,558
I can't heal her.

87
00:05:54,559 --> 00:05:55,759
Nonsense.

88
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:56,919
Save, save.

89
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:00,039
You have to bring her back to life, so that it can be called save.

90
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:03,040
If she can't be brought to life, how can you say you've saved her?

91
00:06:04,159 --> 00:06:06,479
I can just save her, but not cure her.

92
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:09,919
You have to make her move again now.

93
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:12,999
Move... move...

94
00:06:16,399 --> 00:06:19,679
Since you two ask for no return, then I would leave now.

95
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:22,479
No, no!

96
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,039
You can't...

97
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,118
Chase her back.

98
00:06:25,119 --> 00:06:26,999
A patient like her is hard to find.

99
00:06:31,679 --> 00:06:32,479
Not bad, not bad!

100
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,379
Looks like a soft girl,

101
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:35,878
but act fast and violently when being attacked, A good student!

102
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:37,039
What are you doing?

103
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:39,919
Since you don't want to live, then I can slay you.

104
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,718
Why did you save me?

105
00:06:41,719 --> 00:06:44,319
Right, why would I save you?

106
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:46,399
Then I should slay you.

107
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:08,039
Grandpa, she... she is moving.

108
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:08,838
But,

109
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:10,079
she spitted blood...

110
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:11,080
Is that serious?

111
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:19,959
This way to arouse her desire of survival is a strong pill to sooth her depression.

112
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,640
You've found a snap course!

113
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:29,878
Since it works, then I have something to do on this way.

114
00:07:29,879 --> 00:07:31,438
What?

115
00:07:31,439 --> 00:07:33,760
Grandpa, I...

116
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,839
would be a master soon.

117
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:10,239
The famous Tegin of Eagle Division is resigning.

118
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,319
You said I was a coward.

119
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,639
I think you are more suitable in this title.

120
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:17,799
This is the best chance for you to put me to death.

121
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:18,800
Why did you help me?

122
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:23,520
Believe it or not, I've never wanted to put you to death.

123
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,159
I see you as my biggest rival, indeed.

124
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:30,200
But we were also brothers, weren't we?

125
00:08:31,399 --> 00:08:32,999
I didn't hate you at the beginning.

126
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,718
I've tried my best since young.

127
00:08:37,719 --> 00:08:40,158
I really work hard on battlefields, I fought for Uncle Khan,

128
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:44,239
I tried my best to achieve success and earn the recognition of the whole grassland.

129
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:46,879
But no matter how hard I tried, and how well I behaved,

130
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:49,158
you were always ahead of me.

131
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:51,079
Every time you surpassed me in some aspects.

132
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,359
More and more people are talking behind my back,

133
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:57,158
they were saying that you were better than me.

134
00:08:57,159 --> 00:09:00,719
It seemed like all my efforts were like a joke.

135
00:09:02,719 --> 00:09:05,679
So the more they supported you, the more I hated you,

136
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:08,039
the more I wanted to compete with you.

137
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,979
But after all these things, I found out that

138
00:09:09,980 --> 00:09:11,800
actually I didn't hate you,

139
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:15,600
but myself that was not as good as you.

140
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,479
It was my obsessiveness that led to the situation now.

141
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,040
I admit that it's my fault.

142
00:09:23,199 --> 00:09:25,398
So this is why you saved me?

143
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:29,158
If I really lost you, how boring would it be?

144
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:31,119
Don't expect my forgiveness.

145
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:34,158
I would never forget my mother's death.

146
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:35,638
Then stay and retaliate against me.

147
00:09:35,639 --> 00:09:38,580
I said that, if it worked, you would have been dead now.

148
00:09:42,839 --> 00:09:45,479
Did you leave Eagle Division for Li Changge?

149
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:48,399
The whole Eagle Division is no match for Li Changge?

150
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:52,078
As long as I am the Tegin of Eagle Division,

151
00:09:52,079 --> 00:09:53,879
I will be responsible for it.

152
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:54,880
But Li Changge,

153
00:09:56,500 --> 00:10:01,339
she is the one who I will protect by my life as Ashile Sun.

154
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:03,499
As soon as I settle Eagle Division down,

155
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,900
I will find her even if she is at the end of the world.

156
00:10:09,769 --> 00:10:11,769
I think I know why I always lost to you.

157
00:10:16,610 --> 00:10:17,610
Sher!

158
00:10:19,970 --> 00:10:20,970
Where is Changge?

159
00:10:23,129 --> 00:10:23,888
Tell me now!

160
00:10:23,889 --> 00:10:25,009
Where is she?

161
00:10:31,569 --> 00:10:32,169
Mimi...

162
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:33,729
- Please tell me where she is!
 - Stand up!

163
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:34,489
Please!

164
00:10:34,490 --> 00:10:36,008
Tell me where she is.

165
00:10:36,009 --> 00:10:36,568
Stand up.

166
00:10:36,569 --> 00:10:38,128
You were the last one who saw her.

167
00:10:38,129 --> 00:10:39,529
You must know it.

168
00:10:39,530 --> 00:10:40,530
I...

169
00:10:42,329 --> 00:10:43,929
Mimi!

170
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:44,929
Don't ask him!

171
00:10:44,930 --> 00:10:46,368
He doesn't deserve it!

172
00:10:46,369 --> 00:10:48,169
He won't tell you.

173
00:10:48,170 --> 00:10:49,448
Sher...

174
00:10:49,449 --> 00:10:50,930
I know who you are.

175
00:10:51,930 --> 00:10:54,008
If you have any grudge, just vent it on me!

176
00:10:54,009 --> 00:10:55,689
Changge is innocent.

177
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:04,448
She was in the south,

178
00:11:04,449 --> 00:11:07,169
and saved by a man seemingly from the Central Plains.

179
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:08,969
I have no idea if she is alive or not.

180
00:11:08,970 --> 00:11:10,129
Did you lie to me?

181
00:11:11,769 --> 00:11:13,129
I will never lie to you.

182
00:11:24,290 --> 00:11:26,368
This is what she left when she got saved.

183
00:11:26,369 --> 00:11:27,369
Here you are.

184
00:11:35,530 --> 00:11:37,090
This is Changge's wooden hairpin.

185
00:11:41,769 --> 00:11:43,208
Send Su Yishe to search along the way to the south.

186
00:11:43,209 --> 00:11:45,008
Don't miss any man from the Central Plains.

187
00:11:45,009 --> 00:11:45,609
Yes.

188
00:11:45,610 --> 00:11:46,610
Go quickly!

189
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:55,490
Changge!

190
00:11:57,170 --> 00:11:58,170
Wait for me!

191
00:12:17,689 --> 00:12:19,008
Khatun.

192
00:12:19,009 --> 00:12:21,609
Aunt Alir's remains have been packed up.

193
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:23,050
How should we deal with it?

194
00:12:24,530 --> 00:12:26,368
Burn it up.

195
00:12:26,369 --> 00:12:27,369
Yes.

196
00:12:36,769 --> 00:12:37,768
Khatun.

197
00:12:37,769 --> 00:12:39,329
Are you missing the Central Plains?

198
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:43,889
The willows dance in the breeze in spring,

199
00:12:45,850 --> 00:12:49,209
fireflies fly in the summer's night,

200
00:12:50,769 --> 00:12:53,449
red autumnal leaves drifting along the stream,

201
00:12:54,530 --> 00:13:02,530
the white snow covers the lantern and glass.

202
00:13:07,009 --> 00:13:12,448
The central plain in my memories always has four distinctive seasons.

203
00:13:12,449 --> 00:13:17,050
But in the south, even if it's in winter,

204
00:13:18,610 --> 00:13:25,009
green grasses and trees are always on the lush mountains.

205
00:13:26,809 --> 00:13:29,609
Just because of your longings for your homeland,

206
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:33,368
you gave birth to this trouble-making son.

207
00:13:33,369 --> 00:13:37,688
Your boy is so foolish that he killed Alir!

208
00:13:37,689 --> 00:13:39,089
Fine.

209
00:13:39,090 --> 00:13:41,929
Now no one can keep Sun here, he wants nothing here!

210
00:13:41,930 --> 00:13:43,448
And he is leaving me.

211
00:13:43,449 --> 00:13:46,888
I put Alir in your tent, why didn't you take good care of her?

212
00:13:46,889 --> 00:13:51,610
Now you two are unforgivable for making such a big trouble!

213
00:13:52,610 --> 00:13:54,328
Please calm down, Khan!

214
00:13:54,329 --> 00:13:59,888
Khan... I... I can die for my fault, but Sher...

215
00:13:59,889 --> 00:14:02,929
Sher is always loyal to you, and to the prairie.

216
00:14:02,930 --> 00:14:05,489
Maybe he is not good enough now.

217
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:08,568
But if you give him some time, and wait till he makes progress,

218
00:14:08,569 --> 00:14:11,368
he could take the important mission of the grassland.

219
00:14:11,369 --> 00:14:13,929
Please give him another chance, Khan.

220
00:14:13,930 --> 00:14:15,849
Another chance?

221
00:14:15,850 --> 00:14:17,489
Don't think that Sun leaves,

222
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:21,089
so I could pass all the things to your silly son!

223
00:14:21,090 --> 00:14:24,448
A loser can never be the king of the grassland.

224
00:14:24,449 --> 00:14:27,530
The glory of Khan always belongs to a powerful man!

225
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:33,489
The sad face again!

226
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:35,970
I hate you being like this!

227
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:40,008
From now on, you are grounded for a month.

228
00:14:40,009 --> 00:14:43,009
Together with your silly boy, reflect on your faults deeply!

229
00:14:56,490 --> 00:15:02,009
Remember, from now on, no these stuff again!

230
00:16:12,009 --> 00:16:13,768
Tegin, good news.

231
00:16:13,769 --> 00:16:15,888
We found the people from the Central Plains at the boundary of grasslands.

232
00:16:15,889 --> 00:16:17,609
The guard once inquired a donkey cart,

233
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:20,649
with two men, a young and an old, as well as a young lady in there.

234
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:23,170
The old man said that they were the doctors going to the south.

235
00:16:24,170 --> 00:16:25,170
It must be Changge.

236
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:30,929
Su Yishe, find some more details.

237
00:16:30,930 --> 00:16:31,930
Yes.

238
00:16:34,569 --> 00:16:35,569
That's so great!

239
00:16:41,209 --> 00:16:42,489
Mu Jin.

240
00:16:42,490 --> 00:16:43,489
Stay at Eagle Division.

241
00:16:43,490 --> 00:16:47,049
Just as always, report to me as soon as you get news.

242
00:16:47,050 --> 00:16:47,849
Sun.

243
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:49,289
I want to go with you.

244
00:16:49,290 --> 00:16:51,448
I want to take Mimi with us too.

245
00:16:51,449 --> 00:16:53,329
Many hands make light work.

246
00:16:55,050 --> 00:16:56,489
No.

247
00:16:56,490 --> 00:16:58,768
I need to do it on my own.

248
00:16:58,769 --> 00:17:02,448
The big trouble made by Changge has just been eliminated.

249
00:17:02,449 --> 00:17:06,049
If Khan finds out our action, we will be in trouble.

250
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:08,410
You and Mimi would be better to stay here.

251
00:17:09,769 --> 00:17:10,608
Sun.

252
00:17:10,609 --> 00:17:12,409
What about your wound?

253
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:15,050
I'm quite clear how my wound is now.

254
00:17:16,450 --> 00:17:17,809
Mu Jin.

255
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:20,609
You are the only one I can rely on about Eagle Division.

256
00:17:21,889 --> 00:17:23,368
Fine.

257
00:17:23,369 --> 00:17:25,329
You won't listen to me anyway.

258
00:17:25,330 --> 00:17:27,209
I must owe you something last life.

259
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:28,569
Find her back quickly.

260
00:17:28,570 --> 00:17:30,209
Take care of yourself.

261
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:33,529
By the way, Where is Luo Shiba, who was taken here by Changge?

262
00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:36,608
She has left since the day you came back from the court.

263
00:17:36,609 --> 00:17:38,128
She believed that Changge was alive,

264
00:17:38,129 --> 00:17:39,728
and said that she had to find her.

265
00:17:39,729 --> 00:17:41,409
