453
00:27:17,930 --> 00:27:18,689
- Come on.
 - Help!

454
00:27:18,690 --> 00:27:19,169
No.

455
00:27:19,170 --> 00:27:20,248
Help!

456
00:27:20,249 --> 00:27:21,570
Help! Help!

457
00:27:26,129 --> 00:27:27,209
Don't beat him!

458
00:27:27,210 --> 00:27:28,210
Don't beat him!

459
00:27:37,450 --> 00:27:39,090
You are also the refugees from the north?

460
00:27:40,210 --> 00:27:41,088
Don't be afraid.

461
00:27:41,089 --> 00:27:42,449
He is not a good man.

462
00:27:42,450 --> 00:27:44,368
Just a bad official in the government.

463
00:27:44,369 --> 00:27:46,049
You're lucky to meet us.

464
00:27:46,050 --> 00:27:46,768
Go!

465
00:27:46,769 --> 00:27:48,209
Let's divide our grains!

466
00:27:48,210 --> 00:27:49,210
Go!

467
00:28:02,170 --> 00:28:03,008
Let's go.

468
00:28:03,009 --> 00:28:04,129
Follow them and have a look.

469
00:28:11,290 --> 00:28:13,008
We have food, folks!

470
00:28:13,009 --> 00:28:14,128
We have food!

471
00:28:14,129 --> 00:28:15,488
Mine. mine!

472
00:28:15,489 --> 00:28:17,049
Don't grab mine!

473
00:28:17,050 --> 00:28:18,608
Don't grab mine!

474
00:28:18,609 --> 00:28:19,609
I want it!

475
00:28:22,570 --> 00:28:23,929
Folks!

476
00:28:23,930 --> 00:28:25,449
Look at this bad official!

477
00:28:25,450 --> 00:28:28,888
He was transferring so many grains, but refused to give us any.

478
00:28:28,889 --> 00:28:31,289
How could he do that?

479
00:28:31,290 --> 00:28:33,569
Since he wants to starve us to death,

480
00:28:33,570 --> 00:28:37,529
then it's not wrong for us to grab this!

481
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:38,809
Yes, we were right!

482
00:28:38,810 --> 00:28:39,649
We did a right thing!

483
00:28:39,650 --> 00:28:43,488
Do you know why did they refuse to give us food?

484
00:28:43,489 --> 00:28:44,529
Why? Why?

485
00:28:44,530 --> 00:28:45,209
Why?

486
00:28:45,210 --> 00:28:48,410
Now the distinguished are in power, we normal folks have no way to go.

487
00:28:49,489 --> 00:28:53,809
Now we are in such a disaster, so many innocent people are in trouble.

488
00:28:53,810 --> 00:28:57,368
Those nobles and officials in Luoyang even feed their dogs with meat,

489
00:28:57,369 --> 00:28:59,449
instead of sharing food with poor people.

490
00:28:59,450 --> 00:29:04,488
So even death would not expiate the crimes of these men.

491
00:29:04,489 --> 00:29:05,888
Yes, yes!

492
00:29:05,889 --> 00:29:06,889
You're wrong!

493
00:29:10,729 --> 00:29:12,529
What's wrong?

494
00:29:12,530 --> 00:29:14,968
We have no food now because of the natural disaster.

495
00:29:14,969 --> 00:29:16,569
It's been desolate soil along the way here.

496
00:29:16,570 --> 00:29:18,569
No food can be produced.

497
00:29:18,570 --> 00:29:19,728
We can't avoid the natural disaster,

498
00:29:19,729 --> 00:29:21,248
while man-made calamity is evitable.

499
00:29:21,249 --> 00:29:23,128
Now you grab these grains,

500
00:29:23,129 --> 00:29:25,889
those who are waiting for it would be starved to death.

501
00:29:27,129 --> 00:29:31,209
If not, we would be starved to death.

502
00:29:31,210 --> 00:29:32,368
Yes, yes!

503
00:29:32,369 --> 00:29:33,329
We would die!

504
00:29:33,330 --> 00:29:33,848
Yes!

505
00:29:33,849 --> 00:29:34,689
It would be us instead.

506
00:29:34,690 --> 00:29:36,729
But you should not kill them.

507
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:42,409
They just transferred these grains as asked from afar to earn their wages.

508
00:29:42,410 --> 00:29:44,488
He might need to support a whole family.

509
00:29:44,489 --> 00:29:48,008
They are also the friends, families and brothers of others.

510
00:29:48,009 --> 00:29:50,089
They also have families waiting for him to go back.

511
00:29:55,690 --> 00:29:57,848
What a miserable wretch!

512
00:29:57,849 --> 00:30:00,728
She is taking for the government even in this situation.

513
00:30:00,729 --> 00:30:03,569
If you don't want to eat it, then don't!

514
00:30:03,570 --> 00:30:04,449
Piss off!

515
00:30:04,450 --> 00:30:05,008
Get away!

516
00:30:05,009 --> 00:30:05,768
Get away!

517
00:30:05,769 --> 00:30:06,689
Get away! Don't stay here!

518
00:30:06,690 --> 00:30:07,449
Piss off!

519
00:30:07,450 --> 00:30:08,248
Go! Go!

520
00:30:08,249 --> 00:30:09,128
Piss off!

521
00:30:09,129 --> 00:30:10,488
Piss off!

522
00:30:10,489 --> 00:30:12,209
Come on, distribute the grains.

523
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:13,210
Come on, come on.

524
00:30:21,430 --> 00:30:22,430
Stop.

525
00:30:28,129 --> 00:30:30,050
Grandpa, have you ever seen her?

526
00:30:34,330 --> 00:30:36,248
What happened these days?

527
00:30:36,249 --> 00:30:40,169
Someone asked me with a painting, too.

528
00:30:40,170 --> 00:30:41,689
What a coincidence!

529
00:30:41,690 --> 00:30:44,569
You are looking for the same person.

530
00:30:44,570 --> 00:30:45,570
Where did he go?

531
00:31:09,050 --> 00:31:10,050
Who are you?

532
00:31:16,489 --> 00:31:18,329
It has been a long time since we met.

533
00:31:18,330 --> 00:31:19,330
It's you.

534
00:31:46,290 --> 00:31:49,810
Since you have made it to Yunzhou, please hold on.

535
00:31:50,849 --> 00:31:51,930
I will find you.

536
00:31:59,530 --> 00:32:00,848
It's been a tough time for you.

537
00:32:00,849 --> 00:32:02,809
You haven't even had any water.

538
00:32:02,810 --> 00:32:04,008
Hold on.

539
00:32:04,009 --> 00:32:05,129
We will find the princess.

540
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:35,888
Your Majesty, Hao Du sent a message,

541
00:32:35,889 --> 00:32:39,329
Princess Yongan once appeared in Yunzhou.

542
00:32:39,330 --> 00:32:42,369
It's said that she went to Luoyang with a refugee.

543
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:51,050
Okay.

544
00:32:52,969 --> 00:32:56,849
I knew that Yan would be alright.

545
00:32:57,930 --> 00:32:59,809
Mr. Du, please stand up!

546
00:32:59,810 --> 00:33:01,329
Pass my order,

547
00:33:01,330 --> 00:33:04,608
Dispatch more people to find Yan in Yunzhou and Luoyang.

548
00:33:04,609 --> 00:33:06,209
